
[1]turpitude

   TURP'ITUDE, n. [L. turpitudo, from turpis, foul, base.]

   1. Inherent baseness or vileness of principle in the human heart;
   extreme depravity.

   2. Baseness or vileness of words or actions; shameful wickedness.
